title: Theodore Roosevelt Birthplace National Historic Site: Brochures
body: Brochures         Theodore Roosevelt was the Assistant Secretary of the Navy from 1897-1898 and helped prepare for the Spanish-American War. Theodore resigned a few weeks after hostilities began and actively participated in combat as Lieutenant Colonel of the Army's First Volunteer 'Rough Rider' Cavalry Regiment. U.S. Navy  To request brochures for this site, please call 212-260-1616, or write to us at: Theodore Roosevelt Birthplace N.H.S., 28 East 20th Street, New York, NY 10003.
